  "systemName": "CoffeePOS",
  "systemDisplayName": "Coffee Shop POS",
  "systemSpecification": "This system is the point-of-sale software for a small coffee shop. It handles the full lifecycle of a customer order: creation by the barista, modification while the customer is still at the counter, payment authorization against an external card reader, and fulfilment (ticket printed for the kitchen staff, receipt printed for the customer).\n\nThe system is decomposed into two components. The OrderManager is the behavioural core, tracking an order through its states. The InventoryTracker maintains the stock levels for each item sold and flags low-stock conditions back to the OrderManager so items can be struck from the menu.\n\nFour external handlers are wired into the system: a card reader providing synchronous payment authorization, a thermal printer for receipts and kitchen tickets, a customer-facing display, and a database used for long-term order history. Handlers communicate with the components either asynchronously (via interfaces and messages) or synchronously (via handler function calls).\n\nAll monetary amounts are in minor currency units (cents). All time values are in milliseconds unless otherwise noted. Identifier strings are opaque and system-generated."
}